\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 Although it was harvest time, the village had nothing to harvest. They had not pla
nted that year because there was no rain. The previous year had been the last of the years of plenty.
\par When the rain came, it was too little. The villagers had therefore to buy maize from Chembiya. He had maize, groundnuts and rice. Despite the threat of a drought, he had }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\ul\insrsid6047505\charrsid14909436 
hired}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505  men to prepare his three maize fields, two groundnut fields and a large rice field. People had thought he was crazy then, but during this time they all admired him.
\par It was during this harvest time that Chembiya\rquote s wife had another miscarriage. It was the third time. The first time, a baby boy died during delivery. 
\par \'93The man is unfaithful,\'94 accused relations of the wife.
\par There was a second miscarriage. It was a baby girl. It was born on a Saturday at dawn. By morning, before the dew was gone, it was dead. 
\par When it happened the third time, he was furious. Why should it be him? Every family in the village had children except his. 
\par \'93Chembiya!\'94 called his younger brother, Che Saidi. \'93The spirits are speaking through our sister. They say they have a message for you.\'94
\par Chembiya rushed to his sister\rquote s hut. He found her }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\ul\insrsid6047505\charrsid14909436 lying}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 
 on a mat. She was still calling out Chembiya.
\par \'93He is here, he is here,\'94 said Che Ali, Chembiya\rquote s uncle.
\par \'93I am the spirit of
 your mother. Your father and I are angry with you. We are the one visiting your house and we will do so if you do not change. Your father and I need a descent lodging. We are hungry and thirsty. If you do not give us these, you too shall never rest.\'94

\par Chembiya was frightened. He }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\ul\insrsid6047505\charrsid3759326 saw what was behind}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 
 the miscarriages. He believed it was his dead parents.  
\par His parents had died six years ago when he was away to TEBA in South Africa. He was away for three years. When he came back, rich, he never spared anything for them, not even a prayer. They must be really angry with him.
\par The next day he went to the graveyard with other men and his relations. They built a }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505      }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 
tombstone on each of the graves. He planted flowers before they left for home.  At home, he prepared
 a big feast, sadaka. He slaughtered the fattest cow, five goats and ten chickens. There was nsima, rice and thobwa. His sister was the overall in-charge for the kitchen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 In the late summer of that year, Chembiya\rquote 
s wife conceived again. This time, there was great expectation. The family had made peace with the dead. The spirits which had been taking the children in the past now }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\ul\insrsid6047505\charrsid3759326 
lay asleep}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 . 
\par On the ninth month, midwives gathered at Chembiya\rquote s house. Soon the dead baby boy was born. They immediately buried it quietly and quickly. 
\par \'93What is it? What must we do?\'94 asked Abiti Joni, his wife, after some days. 
\par \'93I know there is someone behind all this. Someone is playing tricks with me,\'94 Chembiya }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505        }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 said. 
\par \'93I have been thinking about that too,\'94 added Abiti Joni. \'93But what can we do?\'94 she asked.
\par \'93Well, we will have to go to Chilindi and consult Cheng\rquote ambi, the sing\rquote anga. He may tell us the truth.\'94
\par \'93I have been thinking about that too,\'94 she said feeling relieved.  
\par Cheng\rquote ambi himself looked as strange as the paraphernalia. Short, small with a deep voice bigger than his size, he was wearing a white robe that dwarfed him further. He wore a black collar and a hat with horns on each side. 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid3759326 Chembiya }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 
did not ask questions or give greetings to the patients or enquirers as they took their turns in front of him. When Chembiya and his wife\rquote s turn came, he told them that he knew why they had come. He went to the mirror and rubbing some }{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\ul\insrsid6047505\charrsid3759326 concoctions }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 on it he showed to Chembiya and his wife to see for themselves the }{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\ul\insrsid6047505\charrsid3759326 source of their misery}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs24 \ltrch\fcs0 \f0\fs24\insrsid6047505\charrsid6047505 . 
\par It was an unbelievable sight. His three brothers, the uncle and his sister all appeared sitting in a circle. Each held a club in their hands. A baby appeared in the middle
 and was quickly hit on the head by his sister. Then another came and was hit by his uncle. The third and fourth were hit by two of his brothers. After this they all sat apparently waiting for the next, ready to attack. 
\par \'93Why do this to me?\'94 he asked no on
e in particular. He remembered all the money, blankets and clothes he had given each of these relations when he came back from South Africa. He had always shared maize to them when they were hit by hunger. He could not believe this cruelty. 
\par It was obvious that he was rich and if he were to die leaving children behind, they would be the ones to inherit the wealth. This was definitely the reason for all these killings. 
\par Chembiya pleaded for assistance.
